                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.506/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Collier</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-09-27T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 27, 1927—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>47. Your 138, September 21, 3 p.m. As there is no discrimination against American
                    concerns there is no apparent ground for a formal protest but in your discretion
                    you may continue to urge <pb facs="0634" n="548" xml:id="pg_548"/> informally
                    that the provision in question be eliminated upon the ground that it would
                    interfere with business between the two countries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
